(323, 'Analysis by dev - 2026-01-08: ### Company Snapshot Problem & solution OpusCollect positions itself as an AI-first full-stack collections platform aimed at moving from pre-delinquency to hard-bucket collections, addressing a market with fragmented pan-India field operations and little scale in field-based collections. Market notes emphasize a gap in pan-India field collectors and a shift toward AI-enabled, data-driven recovery processes for banks and NBFCs. Ideal customer profile and pricing Direct clients include Unity Bank, Jana Bank, Avanti Finance, BikeBazaar, Branch, with additional through-partner channels (Fusion, ESAF, Cashe). Total assets under management ~₹900 crore; monthly collections ~₹6 crore. Pricing signals: - Take rates reported as 10% regular, 15% SMA, 20% for 90+ DP buckets. - Revenue drivers indicate 60–70% commission from collections, 15–18% automated legal services, 5–8% AI-driven collections, 2–8% data enrichment; for >90DPD, commissions can be 25–35% of amount collected. - For Kissht, a go-live target of ₹1 crore per month billing is noted. [Inference] Pricing appears to mix performance-based commissions with verticalized service fees; no formal external pricing sheet disclosed. Status of product & traction highlight Live, multi-channel field operations with AI/automation components: - In-house bot calling, route optimization, automated case allocation, and digital legal workflow. - Android field-collection app; real-time field tracking; 64k digital leg...'),
(324, 'Heads up note from @Rahul Mathur 2025-08-23T15:18:00.000+05:30: Hi team, Sharing the heads-up note for our investment in [Orange Slice AI](https://www.ycombinator.com/companies/orange-slice). The company provides AI agents that find you customers who show demand signals - the agents crawl the internet for signals/firmographic data that help sales teams find high-intent prospects by continuously monitoring the internet for buying signals and firmographic changes DeVC is investing $250K as part of a post-YC SAFE round at a $25M cap with MFN clause **Founders** 1. [Kishan Sripada](https://www.linkedin.com/in/kishansripada/) (Co-Founder & CTO) 1. 1 YOE as SDE Intern @ Ramp 1. Ran a successful dance formation app used by Disney, Broadway, Lakers etc 1. Ran an “Airbnb for kitchen space” business during COVID 1. Market making platform connecting unused restaurant kitchens with home cooks 1. Sold to restaurant chain Bravo for $150K 1. Ref from Ramp Manager: "Good kid but young and hard market” 1. In context: "This guy (the manager) is harsh so even a terse vote of approval like this is strong!” 1. UMich ‘25 - dropout 1. [Vihaar Nandigala](https://www.linkedin.com/in/vihaarnandigala/) (Co-Founder & CEO) 1. Left $500K TC placement at JPMC to start this business 1. UMich ‘25 - dropout **Investing Process** 1. This was sourced by simultaneously DeVC IP team (YC mining) & Z47 Enterprise AI team 1. Ashwin & Krish did the 1st call from a Product Eval POV - post which he shared with the wide...')
